"Sure thing! I will set an appointment up for you right away."
Me: "No, I have been experiencing some symptoms and wanted to make sure it was not an emergency."
Medical Assistant: "Okay, well you could try the urgent care a few blocks away. They can handle this kind of thing."
Me: "Hmmm. Okay. Thanks. I appreciate your help."
I hang up.
I think to myself, "That was bizarre. I just got off the phone with the office of the doctor I have been seeing my whole life and she couldn't even be bothered to return my call?"
That was the beginning of the end.
I go to google maps, and find the address of the urgent care. I make sure to write down the phone number. I head over.
They were wonderful!
Yes, the waiting room was packed. Yes, the room I ended up in was small and cramped. Yes, I felt a bit uncomfortable that the door didn't really close completely. But, my doctor was kind and made me feel like I was not going to die. He said I might have strep...and tested me for a bunch of other things. We figured out things to try that would possibly help to see me through the night.
He gave me a script. Even though he didn't think they would fulfill it at the urgent care. I still had to get it there and then try to locate a nearby 24hour pharmacy.
It was a bit of a hassle, but not impossible. I felt much better.
I got home around 10pm. I made a sandwich because I was hungry and headed to bed. I tossed and turned all night. At some point, I had to try the restroom. I felt like I was going to pass out when I got up.
I don't know how I was able to drive myself and make it to work
